abstract: Labor Dept reports weekly applications for unemployment benefits fell 5,000 to seasonally adjusted 267,000, nearing 42-year low as labor market tightens; decline could be attributed to difficulties in adjusting claims during holidays.
lead_paragraph: The number of Americans filing for unemployment benefits fell more than expected last week, nearing a 42-year low as labor market conditions continued to tighten.

headline.main: Jobless Claims Near 42-Year Low as Labor Market Tightens
headline.print_headline: Business Briefing; New Unemployment Claims Fall to Near a 42-Year Low
